Nonlinear fixed effects covariance matrix: non-proportional slowing model

Source: R/vcov.R
vcov.pmrm_fit_slowing.Rd

Extract the covariance matrix of the non-proportional slowing model.

Usage

# S3 method for class 'pmrm_fit_slowing'
vcov(object, ...)

Arguments

object

A fitted model object of class "pmrm_fit" produced by pmrm_model_decline() or pmrm_model_slowing().

...

Not used.

Value

A matrix with covariance of each pair of theta parameters. Rows and columns are labeled by study arm and scheduled visit.

See also

Other estimates and predictions: VarCorr.pmrm_fit(), coef.pmrm_fit_decline(), coef.pmrm_fit_slowing(), fitted.pmrm_fit_decline(), fitted.pmrm_fit_slowing(), plot.pmrm_fit(), pmrm_estimates(), pmrm_marginals(), predict.pmrm_fit(), residuals.pmrm_fit(), vcov.pmrm_fit_decline()

Examples

  set.seed(0L)
  simulation <- pmrm_simulate_slowing(
    visit_times = seq_len(5L) - 1,
    gamma = c(1, 2)
  )
  fit <- pmrm_model_slowing(
    data = simulation,
    outcome = "y",
    time = "t",
    patient = "patient",
    visit = "visit",
    arm = "arm",
    covariates = ~ w_1 + w_2
  )
  vcov(fit)
